A small utility to perform user-configurable actions based on clipboard
contents.

INSTALLATION:

$ git clone <repo>
$ cd opensel
$ mkdir -p ~/bin; cp opensel ~/bin
$ mkdir -p ~/lib/opensel; cp -r patterns plugins ~/lib/opensel
$ cp openselrc ~/.openselrc

REQUIREMENTS

Linux, Solaris, OpenSolaris:

    - xsel - http://www.niksula.hut.fi/~vherva/xsel/

Mac OS:

    - Automator Service
        - Unzip "Smart Clipboard.zip" from the contrib/ directory and copy into
          your ~/Library/Services directory
        - [Recommended] Set up a keyboard shortcut.
          - Instructions on setting up keyboard shortcuts in Snow Leopard:
            http://www.maclife.com/article/howtos/how_master_services_snow_leopard
          - The name of the service would be "Smart Clipboard"
          - I use the shortcut Command-Control-A
